# UI Rules

## Shell separation — hard rule

**Customer shell:** `components/SiteShell.tsx` + `components/PrimaryNav.tsx`
**Admin shell:** `app/admin/layout.tsx` + `app/admin/AdminNav.tsx`

Never use customer shell components inside admin pages.
Never use admin nav inside customer pages.
These are completely separate UI trees.

## Admin nav items (do not add to customer nav)
Dashboard → `/admin`
Customers → `/admin/customers`
Leads → `/admin/leads`
Billing / Revenue → `/admin/revenue`
Log out → `/logout`

## Customer-facing copy — never expose

| Don't use | Use instead |
|---|---|
| "invoice" | "payment" |
| "subscription_id" / "stripe_customer_id" | (never show IDs) |
| "past_due" | "payment issue" or "please update your billing" |
| "trialing" | "trial period" |
| "RunPod job" / "generation_request_id" | (never show) |
| Raw error messages / stack traces | "Something went wrong. Please try again." |
| HTTP status codes | Human-readable message |
| "customer portal" | "billing settings" |

## Interactive states — required for all forms and async actions

Every button or form must handle all three:
- **Loading** — disable button, show spinner
- **Success** — inline confirmation message or state change
- **Error** — inline error message (not console.log, not alert())

Prevent double-submit: disable the submit button while loading.

## Shared components (components/)

| Component | Use |
|---|---|
| `SiteShell.tsx` | Customer layout wrapper |
| `PrimaryNav.tsx` | Customer top nav |
| `AuthNav.tsx` | Auth-aware nav |
| `AuthAwarePrimaryCta.tsx` | CTA aware of session state |
| `OnlyTwinsAssistant.tsx` | AI chat widget |
| `PremiumCard.tsx` | Pricing/plan cards |
| `PremiumButton.tsx` | Premium-styled button |
| `AnimatedBackground.tsx` | Background animation |
| `PageTransition.tsx` | Page transition |
| `BeforeAfterSlider.tsx` | Before/after comparison |
| `BlurredNSFWCard.tsx` | NSFW content blur overlay |
| `GalleryCategoryTabs.tsx` | Gallery filter tabs |

Use existing components before creating new ones.
Co-locate new components with their page if they're only used in 1-2 places.
Move to `/components/` when shared across 3+ pages.

## NSFW content

- Use `BlurredNSFWCard` for sensitive content in galleries
- Never show unblurred NSFW to unauthenticated users
- Gated by `isSubscriber` from `lib/entitlements.ts`

## No placeholder content in production

- No "Coming soon" pages
- No Lorem Ipsum
- No buttons that don't function
- No debug text

## Design standards

- Premium, uncluttered — every element must earn its place
- Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes
- Framer Motion for transitions and animations (see `PageTransition.tsx`)
- Dark mode considered on all new UI
- No tiny fragmented boxes unless they convey distinct information
